  "text": "An appropriate subspace is based on the high-dimensional embedding (HDE) that we have already used in [CITATION_1] . This HDE comprises m axes X 1 , . . . , X m ∈ R n . In order to construct it, we choose m pivot nodes p 1 , p 2 , . . . , p m that are uniformly distributed over the graph and link each of the m axes with a unique node. The axis X i , which is associated with pivot node p i , represents the graph from the \"viewpoint\" of p i . This is done by assigning the j-th component of X i to the graph-theoretical distance between nodes p i and j (i.e., the length of the shortest path connecting the two nodes). Henceforth, we denote this graph-theoretical distance by D pij , so in symbols",
